01:03.363 --> 01:17.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Turkey's capital
city is alive
with fear and anger tonight,
after a car bomb

01:17.411 --> 01:20.914 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
killed at least 28 people and
wounded 61.

01:21.014 --> 01:26.653 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have a report on the blast in
central Ankara,
from Juliet Bremner of
Independent Television

01:26.753 --> 01:28.488 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
News.

01:28.588 --> 01:33.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIET BREMNER: Moments after an
explosion
was heard across the Turkish
capital, flames

01:33.627 --> 01:40.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
leapt into the night sky. The
bomb had hit
a convoy of military buses that
had been taking

01:40.133 --> 01:43.303 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
soldiers home from their
barracks.

01:43.403 --> 01:50.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the chaos immediately after
the attack,
the governor said that he
believed the bomb

01:50.877 --> 01:57.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
had been left in a car. It was
rush hour.
Commuters broke their journey
home to try

01:57.284 --> 02:03.724 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and help move a parked car that
was blocking
the emergency services. Unable
to access the

02:03.824 --> 02:09.062 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
vehicle, they smashed in through
the window
and drove it away.

02:09.162 --> 02:14.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The buses were targeted close to
the Turkish
Parliament. The prime minister,
president,

02:14.167 --> 02:19.072 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and security minister were in
the middle of
a security meeting about Syria
when the bomb

02:19.172 --> 02:27.981 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
went off. This is the fourth
terrorist attack
on Turkey in recent months.

02:28.081 --> 02:34.454 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last October, more than 100
peace activists
were killed during a rally in
Ankara. On that

02:34.554 --> 02:40.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
occasion, the so-called Islamic
State were
blamed. On this occasion, early
indications

02:40.494 --> 02:45.899 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
suggest it could be the work of
the Kurdish
separatist group the PKK,
striking at the

02:45.999 --> 02:51.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
heart of Turkey days after their
army had
hit Kurds across the Syrian
border.

02:51.538 --> 02:56.943 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And in Syria
today, convoys
carrying humanitarian aid made
their way to

02:57.044 --> 03:01.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
besieged parts of the country.
It is part
of an agreement between the
Assad government

03:01.481 --> 03:07.687 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and the U.N. One convoy arrived
in Madaya,
a town west of Damascus that has
been sealed

03:07.788 --> 03:13.360 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
off by government forces for
months. Locals
say dozens of people have
starved to death.

03:13.460 --> 03:19.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Pope Francis spent
this final
day of his visit to Mexico near
the U.S. border.

03:19.533 --> 03:25.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He journeyed to Ciudad Juarez,
just across
the Rio Grande from El Paso,
Texas, and once

03:25.138 --> 03:28.075 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a cauldron of violence and drug
trafficking.

03:28.175 --> 03:33.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The pontiff's first stop was at
a prison,
where he embraced inmates and
preached a message

03:33.180 --> 03:34.981 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of redemption.

03:35.082 --> 03:38.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
POPE FRANCIS, Leader of Catholic
Church (through
translator): The one who has
suffered the

03:38.718 --> 03:44.825 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
greatest pain, and we could say
has experienced
hell, can become a prophet in
society. Work,

03:44.925 --> 03:49.563 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so that this society, which uses
people and
discards them, will not go on
claiming victims.

03:49.663 --> 03:54.534 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The final event of
the papal trip
was a huge outdoor mass this
evening.

03:54.634 --> 04:00.373 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Tensions in the
South China
Sea escalated today, as U.S. and
Taiwan officials

04:00.474 --> 04:06.546 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
confirmed that China has
deployed advanced
surface-to-air missiles on a
disputed island.

04:06.646 --> 04:13.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The batteries are on Woody
Island in the Paracels
claimed by Taiwan and Vietnam,
but controlled

04:13.487 --> 04:15.288 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
by Beijing.

04:15.388 --> 04:18.024 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WANG YI, Chinese Foreign
Minister (through
translator): China's move of
setting up limited,

04:18.125 --> 04:22.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
necessary and self-defense
facilities on the
islands and reefs where Chinese
troops are

04:22.429 --> 04:27.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
stationed is in line with the
right of self-defense
endowed by international law to
any sovereign

04:27.701 --> 04:29.736 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
state. Therefore, there is
nothing wrong about
it.

04:29.836 --> 04:33.840 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But the United
States sharply
criticized the move.

04:33.940 --> 04:38.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Secretary of State John Kerry
spoke in Washington
as he met with Poland's foreign
minister.

04:38.745 --> 04:43.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KERRY, U.S. Secretary of
State: When
President Xi was here in
Washington, he stood

04:43.717 --> 04:51.158 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
in the Rose Garden with
President Obama and
said China will not militarize
in the South

04:51.258 --> 04:58.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
China Sea. But there is every
evidence, every
day, that there has been an
increase of militarization

04:58.632 --> 05:02.502 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of one kind or another. It's of
serious concern.

05:02.602 --> 05:08.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The news came
just a day after
President Obama called for a
peaceful resolution

05:08.608 --> 05:10.544 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of disputes in the South China
Sea.

05:10.644 --> 05:15.982 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Iran pushed back
today against
a proposal to limit supply and
boost prices.

05:16.082 --> 05:21.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
