South Africa ended apartheid.
And while the

37:08.526 --> 37:14.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
country has made progress
towards reconciling
years of state-sanctioned,
violent oppression,

37:14.566 --> 37:16.401 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the reckoning continues.

37:16.501 --> 37:21.406 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the same time, there have
been smaller,
individual efforts to do
penance.

37:21.506 --> 37:26.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, special correspondent
Martin Seemungal
brings us the story of a man who
was once

37:26.644 --> 37:31.382 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the very symbol of apartheid, as
he tries
to make amends.

37:31.483 --> 37:39.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: It is an
unusual scene in
South Africa, a white man in his
late '70s

37:40.058 --> 37:44.729 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in a black township delivering
free food to
the needy.

37:44.829 --> 37:53.138 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it's not just what the man
is doing. It's
who the man is or, who he was.
His name is

37:53.238 --> 37:59.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Adriaan Vlok, and he was a
cabinet minister
during the harshest years of
apartheid, known

37:59.244 --> 38:03.448 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as a ruthless defender of white
minority rule
over the black majority.

38:03.548 --> 38:07.952 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MONDLI MAKHANYA, City Press:
Adriaan Vlok
was the manifestation of the
evil that the

38:08.052 --> 38:12.157 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
apartheid regime was. And he was
the worst
of the worst.

38:12.257 --> 38:18.463 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: Mondli
Makhanya was an anti-apartheid
activist then. Today, he is an
outspoken editorial

38:18.563 --> 38:20.298 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
writer for a Johannesburg
newspaper.

38:20.398 --> 38:28.873 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MONDLI MAKHANYA: From the
mid-1980s, I would
venture to say, other than
President P.W.

38:28.973 --> 38:35.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Botha at the time, he was the
most evil man
in South Africa, and he was the
face of the

38:35.847 --> 38:38.917 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
evil of the apartheid regime.

38:39.017 --> 38:47.692 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: As minister of
law and order,
Vlok was responsible for the
police, the shock

38:47.792 --> 38:55.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
troops in the war against black
activists
fighting apartheid. A bloody,
violent fight,

38:55.967 --> 39:02.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
thousands were killed. Tens of
thousands were
detained, locked up without
trial, all under

39:02.907 --> 39:04.309 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the watch of Adriaan Vlok.

39:04.409 --> 39:07.178 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Adriaan Vlok, Former South
African Minister
of Law and Order: Hello.

39:07.278 --> 39:11.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: Three decades
later now,
in the black township of
Olievenhoutbosch,

39:11.683 --> 39:15.687 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Vlok passes unrecognized as he
does his rounds.

39:15.787 --> 39:21.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Vlok visits this township every
week, delivering
food donated by local
supermarkets to three

39:21.359 --> 39:27.232 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
day care centers and a charity
for the disabled.
He is reaching out to the people
he once helped

39:27.332 --> 39:32.036 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
oppress to atone for what he
calls the sin
of apartheid.

39:32.136 --> 39:40.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Vlok has always been a devout
Christian, but
in the early years, he believed
in white superiority.

39:40.511 --> 39:45.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His transformation began after
the fall of
apartheid and the first all-race
elections.

39:45.683 --> 39:50.321 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Over a period of about 10 years,
he began
to rethink and ultimately
repent.

39:50.421 --> 39:56.594 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADRIAAN VLOK: I told about my
sins. I submitted
to the lord and said, lord, I
have sinned.

39:56.694 --> 39:59.264 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Here I am. Please forgive me.

39:59.364 --> 40:04.736 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I am not offering any excuses. I
cannot offer
an excuse that this and this
were the reason

40:04.836 --> 40:09.140 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
why I did that. I am -- I am
guilty. I am
sorry. Will you please forgive
me?

40:09.240 --> 40:15.580 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: So, his
mission today is
about redemption. It's about
reconciliation.

40:15.680 --> 40:21.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Forty-three-year-old Dinah
Sekese runs the
disabled center Vlok is helping.
As an 18-year-old,

40:22.086 --> 40:26.557 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
she joined the protests against
the apartheid
regime. She knew who he was.

40:26.658 --> 40:32.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DINAH SEKESE, Volunteer Relief
Worker: I know
the man was -- that Adriaan
Vlok, for me,

40:32.630 --> 40:34.332 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
was a bad man.

40:34.432 --> 40:37.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: In the several
years she
has worked with Vlok, she never
showed him

40:37.101 --> 40:43.741 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the scars from the rubber
bullets fired by
his police in 1986, but, on this
day, she

40:43.841 --> 40:48.146 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
did. She told him it happened
during a march
on a police station.

40:48.246 --> 40:50.014 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DINAH SEKESE: Stones go...

40:50.114 --> 40:52.317 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ADRIAAN VLOK: From behind you.

40:52.417 --> 40:58.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DINAH SEKESE: ... over me. And I
was like
-- and then I hear pop, pop,
pop, pop, in

40:58.823 --> 41:07.165 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the front. And almost eight
rubber bullets
hit me. My arms, or you can see
all over,

41:07.265 --> 41:08.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
here.

41:09.033 --> 41:14.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADRIAAN VLOK: I can't take away
that scar,
but I can love her and I can
help her.

41:15.006 --> 41:22.113 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: Painful
memories for Dinah,
poignantly ironic that Adriaan
Vlok is the

41:22.213 --> 41:26.284 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
one offering comfort.

41:26.384 --> 41:32.056 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Obviously, they were police
under your ultimate
command.

41:32.156 --> 41:39.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADRIAAN VLOK: Yes. Yes. I feel
bad. I didn't
feel good about that. I feel
sorry that this

41:39.364 --> 41:45.169 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
has happened. And, as I said, I
can't take
away their scars. They are
there. They are

41:45.269 --> 41:48.139 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there as a witness to what we
did to these
people.

41:48.239 --> 41:53.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: The most
infamous case linked
to Vlok was the attempt to
assassinate Frank

41:53.478 --> 41:56.047 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Chikane.

41:56.147 --> 42:00.785 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Reverend Frank Chikane was a key
member of
the anti-apartheid leadership.
In the late

42:00.885 --> 42:04.455 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
'80s, the apartheid government
saw him as
a significant threat.

42:04.555 --> 42:10.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Did you give the instruction to
kill Frank
Chikane? Or was that -- how did
that come

42:11.062 --> 42:12.797 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
about? Who made that decision?

42:12.897 --> 42:16.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADRIAAN VLOK: His name was put
before me,
and I said there is an
instruction that you

42:16.934 --> 42:22.974 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
could consider killing him. And
I said, do
it, so I pass it on.

42:23.074 --> 42:29.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: Vlok says he
didn't know
how or when it would be done. In
1989, Chikane's

42:29.981 --> 42:33.217 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
clothes were laced with poison.
He barely
survived.

42:33.317 --> 42:40.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In 2006, Vlok confessed to his
involvement
in and was given a 10-year
suspended sentence.

42:40.224 --> 42:46.697 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But he wanted to do more, an act
to underscore
his sincerity. In a private
meeting with Chikane,

42:46.798 --> 42:50.768 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he offered to wash his feet.
Vlok admits he
was afraid.

42:50.868 --> 42:58.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADRIAAN VLOK: I have been a guy
in this country
who had power. I was a minister.
And I am

42:58.476 --> 43:07.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Afrikaans-speaking, and I am a
white man.
And here I am going to bow down
on my knees

43:07.585 --> 43:09.487 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in front of a black man.

43:09.587 --> 43:14.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I stuttered. And I asked him
the question,
"Will you please allow me to
wash your feet?"

43:14.459 --> 43:17.929 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he was taken aback. He said,
"But why
do you want to do that?"

43:18.029 --> 43:24.268 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then we talk a little bit. I
said, "Frank,
I believe that I have hurt you
through apartheid

43:24.368 --> 43:28.005 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and through what we did to you
and your family."

43:28.105 --> 43:32.910 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He said to me, "OK, you can wash
my feet."

43:33.010 --> 43:36.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I cried. And I think Frank
cried. And
he prayed, and I prayed.

43:36.681 --> 43:41.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: The people who
work with
Vlok in the township do not
doubt his sincerity.

43:41.152 --> 43:45.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DINAH SEKESE: And they say, can
you believe
Adriaan Vlok can change? I said,
I believe

43:45.823 --> 43:53.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
what I saw. What I see is what I
believe,
and then I am ready to tell that
Adriaan Vlok

43:53.564 --> 43:54.765 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
has changed.

43:54.866 --> 43:56.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: And they
believe he should
be forgiven.

43:56.701 --> 44:03.140 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DINAH SEKESE: Here in our
country, the only
thing that we appreciate is when
a person

44:03.241 --> 44:10.081 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
comes out and says, sorry. Can
you please
forgive me? It's what we want.
And I believe

44:10.181 --> 44:13.718 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it's something that builds this
peace that
we have in this country.

44:13.818 --> 44:18.389 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: But Mondli
Makhanya says
there is still enormous
bitterness among black

44:18.489 --> 44:23.861 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
South Africans because of the
crimes committed
by the apartheid regime. Not
everyone is willing

44:23.961 --> 44:25.730 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to forgive so easily.

44:25.830 --> 44:31.235 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MONDLI MAKHANYA: Ideally, people
like Adriaan
Vlok should have gone to prison
for a very

44:31.335 --> 44:36.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
long time. But it was necessary,
in the wisdom
of Mandela, that, actually, we
make those

44:36.207 --> 44:39.443 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
compromises. But forgiveness
comes hard.

44:39.544 --> 44:45.116 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADRIAAN VLOK: I think it is of
the utmost
importance, because if you are
not prepared

44:45.216 --> 44:53.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to forgive and to be reconciled,
what is the
-- what is the alternative? It
is hatred,

44:53.424 --> 44:59.263 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I blame you, they blame me, and
we will not
find each other.

44:59.363 --> 45:06.571 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTIN SEEMUNGAL: A scene like
this would
have been unimaginable 30 years
ago, South

45:06.671 --> 45:12.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Africa's most feared apartheid
minister embracing
young black children singing the
national

45:12.843 --> 45:14.745 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
anthem.

45:14.845 --> 45:20.518 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Adriaan Vlok says he will
dedicate his remaining
years to peace and
reconciliation one day

45:20.618 --> 45:23.921 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
at a time.

45:24.021 --> 45:28.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Martin Seemungal
in Olievenhoutbosch Township
near Pretoria,

45:29.026 --> 45:30.995 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
South Africa.

